{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Bearman Glacier | other_name = | photo = Thurston Island - en.svg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Map of Thurston Island | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bearman Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Ellsworth Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|72|21|S|99|10|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Schwartz Cove]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
[[File:ThurstonIsland Terra MODIS.jpg|thumb|280px|Satellite image of Thurston Island.]] '''Bearman Glacier''' ({{Coord|72|21|S|99|10|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] whose head is east of [[Mount Howell]] in central [[Thurston Island]]. The glacier flows south into [[Schwartz Cove]] on the south side of the island. It was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] after [[F.O. Bearman]], Photographer's Mate in the Eastern Group of [[U.S. Navy Operation Highjump]], which obtained aerial photographs of this glacier and adjacent coastal areas, 1946–47.
