A '''thermostad''' is a homogeneous layer of oceanic waters in terms of temperature, it is defined as a relative minimum of the vertical [[temperature gradient]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Tsuchiya|first=Mizuki|date=1986|title=Thermostads and circulation in the upper layer of the Atlantic Ocean|url=https://doi.org/10.1016/0079-6611(86)90040-6|journal=Progress in Oceanography|volume=16|pages=235-267|via=Elsevier ScienceDirect}}</ref>

